px; transform: translateX(0px) translateY(7px);\"></div> <div style=\"background-color: #F4F4F4; height: 12.5px; transform: rotate(-45deg) translateX(3px) translateY(1px); width: 12.5px; flex-grow: 0; margin-right: 14px; margin-left: 2px;\"></div> <div style=\"background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; height: 12.5px; width: 12.5px; transform: translateX(9px) translateY(-18px);\"></div></div><div style=\"margin-left: 8px;\"> <div style=\" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 20px; width: 20px;\"></div> <div style=\" width: 0; height: 0; border-top: 2px solid transparent; border-left: 6px solid #f4f4f4; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; transform: translateX(16px) translateY(-4px) rotate(30deg)\"></div></div><div style=\"margin-left: auto;\"> <div style=\" width: 0px; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-right: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(16px);\"></div> <div style=\" background-color: #F4F4F4; flex-grow: 0; height: 12px; width: 16px; transform: translateY(-4px);\"></div> <div style=\" width: 0; height: 0; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-left: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(-4px) translateX(8px);\"></div></div></div></a> <p style=\" margin:8px 0 0 0; padding:0 4px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tv/B00vl-MHnPn/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" color:#000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none; word-wrap:break-word;\" target=\"_blank\">A fortnight ago, 250 nature lovers, including Nathan Hartono, Aarika Lee and Kevin Lester, came together to clean up one of Singapore’s beaches. They found out that #plasticpollution is no longer only in our seas, but also in our food, water and air. This has put us on a #plasticdiet, with each of us consuming close to 5 grams of plastic each week. We can&#39;t clean up every beach, but we can still change this with your support. Help  us reach out to businesses and governments to stop #plasticpollution from entering our natural systems &#8211; link in bio!</a></p> <p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\">A post shared by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/wwfsg/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px;\" target=\"_blank\"> WWF-Singapore</a> (@wwfsg) on <time style=\" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;\" datetime=\"2019-08-06T13:46:15+00:00\">Aug 6, 2019 at 6:46am PDT</time></p></div></blockquote><script async src=\"//www.instagram.com/embed.js\"></script>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What it means: </strong>But we cannot keep cleaning our beaches <a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/ocean/2018/11/plastic-pollution-opinion-businesses-pact/\">without addressing plastic pollution at source: OURSELVES</a>. 80% of plastic pollution in our oceans comes from land. By mandating governments to act, businesses to comply and consumers to be a part of the solution, a global treaty would have an impact far bigger than any beach clean-up – one where we clean up our act.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>3) You are not alone in caring about plastic</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Already refusing plastic straws? Fab. Bringing reusable items everywhere? Awesome. As you do your part to reduce your use of plastics on a daily basis, it would be comforting to know that <a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/ocean/2019/01/plastic-straw-business-owner-pact-wwf/\">you are not alone in doing so</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/124_20190915_WWFSG_PWP_AZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5412\" srcset=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/124_20190915_WWFSG_PWP_AZ.jpg 1000w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/124_20190915_WWFSG_PWP_AZ-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /><figcaption>In a bid to rally the community to reduce plastic use, our first-ever &#8216;Pay with Plastic&#8217; event saw us through more than 10,000 plastic bottles and 454 customers who added their voice to call for a legally binding global treaty.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What it means: </strong>With a global agreement, there will be plans at the highest levels to ensure governments put money where their mouth is: through investments that change how plastics are produced, used and disposed of. This includes making sure that businesses do their part as well!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is not the first time that a world leader has called for global action on plastic pollution. There has been a growing crescendo of support by leaders to act on the global plastic crisis. This year alone, these voices have come from the G20 (Group of Twenty) nations, as well as regional groups from the Pacific states, the Caribbean and even Southeast Asia.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>So what’s next?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Our use of plastics is expected to double over the next 20 years – a scary thought given that <a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/plastics-in-nature/2019/06/microplastics-plastic-pollution-human-health/\">microplastics from plastic pollution have infiltrated our air, food and water sources</a>. We have to act before that happens. This takes real work.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>World leaders, ministers, mayors and policy makers need to know that we want to see action that fixes plastic pollution once and for all. Add your voice for a legally binding global treaty (1.5 million others and counting have done it) at <a href=\"https://yourplasticdiet.org/sg/\">yourplasticdiet.org/sg</a> to be part of the movement to #StopPlasticPollution.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>A timeline of regional commitments in support of a global treaty to tackle the plastic crisis</strong>:</h4>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-fest-ultra-addons-gutenberg-timeline fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_wrapper\" data-block-version=\"5\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_block\" style=\"background-color:#f8f9fa;background-image:url();background-repeat:repeat;background-size:auto;background-attachment:scroll;border-width:0px;border-color:#ddd;border-radius:10px;border-style:solid\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_layout1\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stages\" style=\"justify-content:center\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_left-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:right\"><strong>March 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:right\">Over 50 countries supported the call for a global treaty at <strong>t</strong>he UN Environment Assembly.</p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">0</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_right-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:left\"><strong>March 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:left\">300,000 people supported WWF’s online petition for a global treaty. <br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">1</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_left-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:right\"><br/><strong>April 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:right\">The Nordic governments became the first to call for a global treaty.<br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">2</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_right-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:left\"><strong>May 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:left\">More than 180 countries (excluding the U.S) agreed to restrict global plastic waste trade at the Basel Convention.<br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">3</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_left-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:right\"><strong>June 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:right\">Leaders of the G20 countries agreed to bring marine plastic pollution to zero by 2050.<br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">4</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_right-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:left\"><strong>June 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:left\">Leaders at the 34th ASEAN Summit &#8211; Singapore included &#8211; committed to regional cooperation on plastic pollution.<br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">5</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_left-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:right\"><strong>August 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:right\">The Pacific states echoed the call for a global treaty to curb plastic pollution at the 50th Pacific Islands Forum Leaders’ Meeting.<br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">6</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_right-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:left\"><strong>October 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:left\">1.5 million people around the world supported WWF’s online petition for a global treaty. <br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">7</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_stage fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_left-side\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_content\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_heading-wrapper\" style=\"height:30px\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_heading_heading\"><h2 style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:21px;text-align:right\"><strong>October 2019</strong></h2></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_common_paragraph_paragraph\"><p style=\"color:#343a40;font-size:16px;text-align:right\">Norway, Sweden and Grenada committed to support a global binding agreement to stop marine plastic pollution at the Our Ocean conference. <br/><br/></p></div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_separator\" style=\"padding-left:30px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:75px\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_line\" style=\"width:3px;background-color:#6c757d\"></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_bullet\" style=\"font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-family:unset;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;color:#f8f9fa;background-color:#343a40;border-radius:50%;width:30px;height:30px;line-height:30px\">8</div></div><div class=\"fest-ultra-blocks_block_timeline_management\" style=\"width:calc(50% - 15px - 30px)\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Help us call for a legally binding global treaty at <a href=\"https://yourplasticdiet.org\">yourplasticdiet.org</a> and use the hashtags <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/uselessplastic/?hl=en\">#uselessplastic</a> and <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/plasticdiet/?hl=en\">#plasticdiet</a>.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Main image:&nbsp;Hermes Rivera&nbsp;on&nbsp;Unsplash</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>If you like reading this, see </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/plastics-in-nature/2019/06/plastic-straws-businesses-timeline-singapore/\"><strong><em>our timeline of how we helped transform the business industry in 18 months</em></strong></a><strong><em>, </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/climate-change/2019/02/environmental-issues-pollution-climate-change/\"><strong><em>why it may be too late if we leave it to our kids to fix the planet</em></strong></a><strong><em> and </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/climate-change/2019/02/environmental-issues-pollution-climate-change/\"><strong><em>the stranded whale with a staggering 5.9kg of plastic in its stomach</em></strong></a><strong><em>. <br></em></strong></p>\n","uri":"plastic-pollution-ocean-beach-clean-up/","author":{"name":"Janissa Ng","slug":"janissa-ng","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/878af2e67bd7d4b058ec3d614d76ab36?s=96&d=mm&r=g"}},"featuredImage":{"altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/hermes-rivera-R1_ibA4oXiI-unsplash.jpg 1000w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/hermes-rivera-R1_ibA4oXiI-unsplash-300x200.jpg 300w"},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"ASEAN summit","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/asean-summit/","slug":"asean-summit"},{"name":"basel convention","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/basel-convention/","slug":"basel-convention"},{"name":"beach cleanup","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/beach-cleanup/","slug":"beach-cleanup"},{"name":"G20","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/g20/","slug":"g20"},{"name":"global treaty","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/global-treaty/","slug":"global-treaty"},{"name":"international coastal cleanup","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/international-coastal-cleanup/","slug":"international-coastal-cleanup"},{"name":"paywithplastic","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/paywithplastic/","slug":"paywithplastic"},{"name":"plastic diet","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/plastic-diet/","slug":"plastic-diet"},{"name":"plastic in nature","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/plastic-in-nature/","slug":"plastic-in-nature"},{"name":"plastic pollution","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/plastic-pollution/","slug":"plastic-pollution"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Plastics in Nature","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/plastics-in-nature/","slug":"plastics-in-nature"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[{"name":"Make Singapore Haze-Free","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/campaign/make-singapore-haze-free/","slug":"make-singapore-haze-free","campaignsTaxonomyFields":{"featureColor":"#da1d52","featureIcon":{"srcSe